   <body>
      <context>
    Editing role information enables you to manage the system's security by defining permissions to a role  and restricting user access to selective modules or forms in the application.</context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click<uicontrol>Administration</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>ADMINISTRATION</uicontrol>page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the navigation pane, expand<uicontrol>User Management</uicontrol>, and then click<uicontrol>Security Roles</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>SECURITY ROLES</uicontrol>list page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the appropriate role, and then click<uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>SECURITY ROLES</uicontrol> page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Update the <uicontrol>Role</uicontrol> and <uicontrol>Description</uicontrol> fields with the appropriate information.</p>
            <p>For information on permissions, refer to<xref href="../Permissions/ConfigRolePerms.xml">Configuring Role Permissions</xref>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click<uicontrol>Save</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
      <div>If the role name is modified, ensure that the associated workflows' stakeholders are updated at every stage.<ph>For information on updating a workflow, refer to <xref href="../../Configuration_Toolkit/Workflow_Management/EditWF.xml">Editing a Workflow</xref> .</ph>
      </div>
